{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01D3MHLrbSWXUqfPBCzuNh1N","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Found the root cause! In the command for crdb-cluster-1:\n\n```\nif [ \"$POD_NAME\" = \"crdb-cluster-1\" ]; then\n  HTTP_ADDR=\"127.0.0.1:8080\";\nelse\n  HTTP_ADDR=\"0.0.0.0:8080\";\nfi\n```\n\nWhen `POD_NAME = crdb-cluster-1`, the `--http-addr` is set to `127.0.0.1:8080` (localhost only). But the liveness and readiness probes use `httpGet` with `port: http` (8080). \n\nKubernetes probes connect to the pod's actual network IP, not localhost, so they can't reach a server bound to 127.0.0.1. The fix is to remove that conditional and always bind to 0.0.0.0:8080 so the health checks can connect properly.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":3519,"cache_read_input_tokens":47598,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":3519},"output_tokens":25,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"b388c552-15bd-47a3-9ea2-b6386747c64f","uuid":"6f84b63f-e274-476b-934c-80ecfd862323","request_id":"req_011CcN5NDAaYSvFt7SA7WLj3"}
